-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
THIRD-PARTY RUNTIME COMPONENTS

The MIT terms above cover all of this project's own code, including its Z80 CPU
and T6W28 PSG emulation cores, which are first-party (clean-room, vendored from
the NGPCraft emulator).

The distributed Windows build bundles the Qt 6 framework and, through Qt
Multimedia, the FFmpeg libraries (avcodec, avformat, avutil, swresample,
swscale). These are NOT covered by the MIT license above and retain their own:

  - Qt 6      : used under the GNU LGPL v3. The Qt DLLs are dynamically linked
                and may be replaced by the end user, as LGPL v3 requires.
                <https://www.qt.io/licensing>  <https://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl-3.0.html>
  - FFmpeg    : LGPL v2.1+ (as shipped by Qt). <https://www.ffmpeg.org/legal.html>

Distributing the built binary therefore means complying with the LGPL for those
components (keep them dynamically linked, allow the user to swap them, and carry
this notice). None of that constrains reuse of this project's own MIT-licensed
source.

